    <h2><a href="../../../symfony-drupal-8-related-issues-posts" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Timeline of Symfony in Drupal 8 related issues and posts">Timeline of Symfony in Drupal 8 related issues and posts</a></h2>
            <span class="timestamp">18 Oct 2012</span>
      </div>
  <div class="content clear-block">
        	<div class="node-author">Posted by admin</div>
            <p>In preparation for <a href="http://2012.drupalcamp.es/es/sesiones/symfony-en-drupal-8-los-detalles-101">my talk at Drupalcamp Spain 2012 about Symfony in Drupal 8</a> I made a list of some relevant issues and posts related to the topic. In pretty much chronological order.</p>
  </div>
      <div class="meta">
                <div class="links"></div>
          </div>
  </div> <!-- node -->
<div id="node-87" class="node  node-story clear-block">
  <div class="node-headline clear-block">
    <h2><a href="../../../barcelona-drupal-developer-days-2012-review" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Barcelona Drupal Developer Days 2012 Review">Barcelona Drupal Developer Days 2012 Review</a></h2>
            <span class="timestamp">19 Jun 2012</span>
      </div>
  <div class="content clear-block">
        	<div class="node-author">Posted by admin</div>
            <p style="margin: 0; float: right;"><span class="inline inline-right"><img src="../../../sites/peterlozano.com/files/imagecache/side_image/ifa_upload/img_5626.jpg" alt="" title=""   /></span>
</p>
<p>The Drupal Developer Days was supposed to be a small event intended for Drupal european developers that wanted to just meet sharing coding ideas.</p>
<p>But when you see:</p>
<ul>
<li> More than 300 drupal developers from several continents, where you can find big names like:
<ul>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/24967">Angie Byron</a> (<a href="http://twitter.com/webchick">@webchick</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/26979">Earl Miles</a> (<a href="http://twitter.com/merlinofchaos">@merlinofchaos</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/4166">Gábor Hojtsy</a> (<a href="http://twitter.com/gaborhojtsy">@gaborhojtsy</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/54136">Daniel Kudwien</a> (<a href="http://twitter.com/tha_sun">@tha_sun</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/4299">Jose Reyero</a> (<a href="https://twitter.com/josereyero">@josereyero</a>)</li>
<li><a href="http://drupal.org/user/16747">Wolfgang Ziegler</a>(<a href="http://twitter.com/the_real_fago">@the_real_fago</a>)</li>
<li>and <a href="http://drupal.org/user/86106">Bojan Zivanovic</a> (<a href="http://twitter.com/bojan_zivanovic">@bojan_zivanovic</a>).</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li> 7 Drupal Core sprints lasting the whole week</li>
<li> and more than 30 technical session</li>
</ul>
<p>then you start to think that this maybe is not so small. And my opinion is that this kind of events will consolidate as a very good alternative to the ever price increasing, overcrowded and more marketing oriented event that has become Drupalcon. And the perfect weather and great nightlife of Barcelona this time of the year made it the best european Drupal event I have attended since quite some time.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.bluesparklabs.com/">Bluespark Labs</a> was one of the sponsors of the event, and team members <a href="http://drupal.org/user/200188">Ronald Ashri</a>, Andrea Poidomani, <a href="http://drupal.org/user/356249">Pablo Cerda</a> and myself (<a href="http://drupal.org/user/123766">Pedro Lozano</a>) attended.</p>
<div class="image-clear"></div>  </div>
      <div class="meta">
                <div class="links"></div>
          </div>
  </div> <!-- node -->
<div id="node-75" class="node  node-story clear-block">
  <div class="node-headline clear-block">
    <h2><a href="../../../camera-drupal-instant-image-distribution" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Camera to Drupal, instant image distribution">Camera to Drupal, instant image distribution</a></h2>
            <span class="timestamp">24 Jul 2010</span>
      </div>
  <div class="content clear-block">
        	<div class="node-author">Posted by admin</div>
            <h2>Abstract</h2>
<p>This posts describes a method to take a picture with a digital camera (preferably a DSLR) and have it instantly uploaded to a Drupal website where it will be imported as an image node. All these steps will be done automatically and you will only need to press the shutter button of your camera for the whole process to start. Continuous shutting is also supported.</p>
<p><span class="inline inline-none"><img src="../../../sites/peterlozano.com/files/imagecache/preview/ifa_upload/camera2drupal.png" alt="" title="Camera to Drupal workflow"   /><span class="caption" style="width: -2px;"><strong>Camera to Drupal workflow: </strong>Trigger the whole process only by clicking the shutter of your camera.</span></span></p>
<div class="image-clear"></div>  </div>
      <div class="meta">
                <div class="links"></div>
          </div>
  </div> <!-- node -->
